When total PSA is in the range of 4.0-10.0 ng/mL, a free
PSA/total PSA ratio <=0.10 indicates 49 to 65% risk of prostate
cancer depending on age; and a free PSA/total PSA ratio >0.25
indicates a 9 to 16% risk of Prostate cancer depending on age.
*Therapeutic range will vary depending on the organ transplanted and the length of time from initial
transplantation and will be determined by the transplant provider or caregiver.
